{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ensure fair grading for GCSE students in 2023",
        "additional_details": "I feel strongly that students have missed out prime learning time over the course of year 8 and sections of year 9. COVID-19 has effected numerous important aspect to education and gaps in learning could mean many students will find some topics more challenging in the exams.\r\n\r\nFor 2022, Ofqual has created a grade distribution that is generous compared to 2019. We want the same arrangements to apply to 2023.",
        "background": "We want the Government to work with Ofqual to ensure that students are graded as generously as they were in 2022, to reflect the disruption caused by covid-19.",
